======================================================================

paexec: Small program that processes a list of tasks in parallel
        on different CPUs, computers in a network or whatever else.
        Full documentation is available in paexec.1 and paexec.pod

author:                                  Aleksey Cheusov <vle@gmx.net>

project's home page:           http://sourceforge.net/projects/paexec/
                                 http://freshmeat.net/projects/paexec/

licence:                                                   MIT license

======================================================================

                             INSTALLATION

See INSTALL file

======================================================================

                           PACKAGES

  1) NetBSD, DragonFlyBSD, Linux, Solaris... (pkgsrc)

    PAEXEC is packaged in pkgsrc as wip/paexec.

  2) FreeBSD

    PAEXEC is packaged in FreeBSD ports as devel/paexec.

  3) Debian/lenny/x86

    Add the following lines

        deb     http://mova.org/~cheusov/pub/debian       lenny    main
        deb-src http://mova.org/~cheusov/pub/debian       lenny    main

    to /etc/apt/sources.list and then using apt or aptitude commands.
    Binary packages are available only for Debian/Lenny/i386.
    Ubuntu users need to recompile the package for their system.
